# git blame ignore-revs file
#
# Lists commits that performed mechanical, repository-wide changes (formatter
# sweeps, codemods, mass renames). Listing them here makes `git blame` and
# the GitHub blame UI skip past these commits, so blame keeps pointing at the
# author of the underlying logic instead of the author of the format sweep.
#
# Local activation (one-time, per developer):
#   git config blame.ignoreRevsFile .git-blame-ignore-revs
#
# GitHub respects this file automatically with no setup required.
#
# Only add commits that contain zero logic changes. False positives
# misattribute authorship.

